{"title":"How to watch the Giro d’Italia 2025","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-and-live-stream-the-giro-ditalia","date":1746698213000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-and-live-stream-the-giro-ditalia\">How to watch the Giro d’Italia 2025</a></p>\n\n<p>It’s finally Grand Tour season. The first three-weeker of the year is the Giro d’Italia, which starts on Friday 9th May and runs until Sunday 1st June. The race will be shown live from start to finish in the UK on TNT Sports, with nightly highlights of free channel Quest.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">2025</a> <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">Giro</a> <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">d’Italia</a> starts outside of Italy for the first time since 2022 with three stages in Albania. After crossing the Adriatic, the racing will move north from Puglia towards the first summit finish in the Apennines and a Strade Bianche gravel stage to round out week one. The real climbing kicks in towards the end of week two, with the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/mortirolo-cycling\">Mortirolo</a> and Monte Grappa scheduled for Stages 16 and 17. To close out the GC fight, the peloton tackles the climbs of the Valle d’Aosta, ending with the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/colle-delle-finestre-cycling\">Colle delle Finestre</a> on Stage 20 before one final trip to Rome on Stage 21.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Primož Roglič starts the Giro as the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-favourites\">slight favourite</a>, with Juan Auyso and Adam Yates breathing down their neck in the bookmakers odds. Other contenders for the <em><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-d-italia-why-jersey-pink\">maglia rosa</a></em> include Jai Hindley, Antonio Tiberi and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/romain-s-road-romain-bardet-profile\">Romain Bardet</a>, who’ll be racing his final Grand Tour.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Where and how to watch the Giro d’Italia 2025</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/GettyImages-2152473027-970x646.jpg\" alt=\"PRATI DI TIVO, ITALY - MAY 11: (L-R) Cian Uijtdebroeks of Belgium and Team Visma | Lease a Bike, Antonio Tiberi of Italy and Team Bahrain - Victorious, Ben O'Connor of Australia and Decathlon AG2R La Mondiale Team, Geraint Thomas of The United Kingdom and Team INEOS Grenadiers, Thymen Arensman of Netherlands and Team INEOS Grenadiers, compete in the breakaway climbing to the Prati di Tivo (1451m) during the 107th Giro d'Italia 2024, Stage 8 a 152km stage from Spoleto to Prati di Tivo 1451m / #UCIWT / on May 11, 2024 in Prati di Tivo, Italy. (Photo by Tim de Waele/Getty Images)\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/GettyImages-2152473027-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/GettyImages-2152473027-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/GettyImages-2152473027-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/GettyImages-2152473027-1536x1023.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/GettyImages-2152473027-2048x1364.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/GettyImages-2152473027-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/GettyImages-2152473027-1140x759.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/GettyImages-2152473027-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/GettyImages-2152473027-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/08/GettyImages-2152473027-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All 21 stages of the Giro d’Italia 2025 will be available to watch in the UK and Ireland on TNT Sports. This will include ‘The Breakaway’ analysis show that will air before and after each stage. If you want an ad-free alternative or to watch on the go, you can stream the racing on Discovery+.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the United States, the racing will be available on Max; FloBikes will provide the coverage over in Canada; and for Australians, the Giro will be shown live on on SBS. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while abroad in countries without access.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If the race isn’t being broadcast in your country or you are travelling abroad, a VPN will allow you to hide your device’s location to access content that is normally geo-blocked. One such VPN provider is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is <a href=\"https://www.techradar.com/reviews/expressvpn\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find free to watch cycling, and costs start from around £5 per month.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/how-to-watch-cycling-for-less-in-the-uk\">How to watch cycling for less in the UK</a></strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Read more:</strong> <strong><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/free-to-air-cycling\">Which countries can watch cycling for free in 2025?</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+5\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-1-970x300.webp\" alt=\"Cyclist banner saying 'celebrate the world's most beautiful sport, click here to subscribe'\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-1-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-1-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-1-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-1-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-1-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-1-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-1-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Full list of broadcasters</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/01/GettyImages-1491743147-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Eurosport</strong>: Pan-Europe (excluding the UK and Ireland), Asia-Pacific (excluding China) and Indian subcontinent</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>TNT</strong> <strong>Sports</strong>: UK and Ireland</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>FloSports/FloBikes</strong>: Canada, Australia</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Max:</strong> USA</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Claro+ &amp; DirecTV</strong>: Latin America &amp; Caribbean</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SBS: </strong>Australia</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>La Chaîne L’Équipe:</strong> France</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>RTBF &amp; VRT</strong>: Belgium</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>RAI</strong>: Italy, San Marino, Vatican City</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>NOS</strong>: Netherlands</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>EITB: </strong>Basque Country</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>S4C:</strong> Wales</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>J Sports:</strong> Japan</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SRG-SSR</strong>: Switzerland</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Starzsport</strong>: Middle East (including Malta and Israel)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Zhibo.tv</strong>: China</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Supersport</strong>: Sub-Saharan Africa (including South Africa)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n 